name: Synapse
description: A synapse is the gap between two nerve cells where impulses are transmitted. In Buddhism, there is a practice of breathing where one focuses on the gap between breaths instead of the breaths themselves. It is this gap – this space between, this space before impulse or breath – that fascinates me. In this digital painting, I wanted to zoom into the synapse and imagine the electric, invisible chemistry that happens there; a moment of infinite potential.
